STAGE — CLIENT WEB (SSR) UI KIT SETUP + HERO ONLY

SCOPE
- Work ONLY in: apps/client-web
- Goal: install/configure Angular Material and add a small hero section to the home page (/).
- Do NOT implement auth, search, booking, cart, payment, invoice, minio, jobs, or any backend changes.

ANGULAR RULES
- This app is Angular SSR.
- NgModule architecture ONLY. Standalone components/bootstrap are strictly forbidden.
- Keep AppModule + AppRoutingModule structure.
- Use SCSS for styling.
- SSR safety: do not use window/document/localStorage directly in components.

UI KIT
- Use Angular Material only (no Tailwind, no extra UI libraries).
- Create a MaterialModule (NgModule) to centralize Material imports.

HOME PAGE HERO REQUIREMENTS
- Route: `/` must render HomeComponent.
- Hero content (exact text):
  - H1: "Biletini Kolayca Bul"
  - Subtitle: "Uçak, otobüs, tur ve araç kiralama seçeneklerini tek yerde karşılaştır."
  - Primary CTA button: "Bilet Ara"
  - Secondary CTA button: "Üye Ol"
- Use Angular Material components:
  - MatButton (required)
  - MatToolbar (optional)
  - MatCard or simple container (optional)
- Add minimal responsive SCSS:
  - max-width container (e.g., 1200px)
  - padding
  - buttons spacing
- Keep it clean and minimal: no over-engineering.

DELIVERABLES
- Angular Material installed and working in SSR build.
- MaterialModule created and imported into AppModule.
- Home page hero visible on `/`.
- App builds/runs in SSR mode without runtime errors.

CONSTRAINTS
- Do NOT convert to standalone.
- Do NOT add feature modules beyond what is needed for home routing and Material setup.
- Keep changes minimal and focused.